From 37ad8d6edbeffa8ca77224f0cfd2d54f6c2baf5f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <quic_hbijlani@quicinc.com>
Date: Mon, 14 Apr 2025 12:26:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/8] wifi: ath12k: Hardware specific ieee80211_ops
 registration

With unified driver, the Tx functionality is split between common and
architecture-specific modules. Defining the ieee80211_ops Tx callback
in the common module introduces additional indirections, as the common
Tx function calls the architecture-specific Tx functions via ops. To
avoid this, the Tx callback should be defined in the architecture-specific
module. This patch establishes the base framework to register the
ieee80211_ops table according to the underlying hardware architecture.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.WBE.1.3.1-00173-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1
Tested-on: WCN7850 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.HMT.1.0.c5-00481-QCAHMTSWPL_V1.0_V2.0_SILICONZ-3

Signed-off-by: Ripan Deuri <quic_rdeuri@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <quic_hbijlani@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Aman Mehta <quic_amanmeht@quicinc.com>
